    "body": "> Right so... the issue with the border is that we can't use a transparent color there because depending on its background it'll look off. Just like it's slightly different in your hovered screenshot.\r\n> \r\n> That's why, in some cases, the border color for the online status needs to get a hardcoded color, really depending on what background the item sits on.\r\n> \r\n> Anyways, that's a different issue (which exists for a long time btw, but has mostly been accounted for in previous implementations of views in desktop. Seems like we lost it with refactors in StatusQ.\r\n> \r\n> In this issue here I see the border disappearing entirely as you can see in my screenshots.\r\n\r\nOuch I'm stupid, that's (sadly yet another) different component; will investigate some more",
